# File Management Rules

## Creation

- Check standardization guidelines before creating files
- Verify no duplicate functionality exists
- Match existing file formats

## Imports

- Verify package structure before adding imports
- Follow import ordering standards:
  1. Standard library imports
  2. Third-party imports
  3. First-party imports (foundation.*)
  4. Local imports (relative)

## Modification

- Preserve existing file format
- Update related files when changing functionality:
  - Update tests
  - Update documentation
  - Update dependent modules
  - Update configuration files

## Directory Management

- Follow standardization guidelines for directory structure
- Verify directory purpose
- Maintain consistent directory hierarchy
- Include required base files (README.md, __init__.py)

## Validation

- Run pre-creation checks before creating new files
- Maintain consistency during updates
